The gunmen who attacked a shopping centre in Kenya, killing at least 67 people, probably died in the attack, an FBI official has said.

Al Qaeda-linked Al-Shabab militants claimed responsibility for the attack on Nairobi’s Westgate Mall on September 21 last year.

